2. In this Law-
"building" includes any structure of whatsoever materials constructed;
"land" includes building-sites, gardens and yards;
"Nicosia Town" means that part of Nicosia comprised within the old walls or ramparts;
"Nicosia water supplies" means all water (whether brought to or running on the surface or not) and all sources, springs, streams or wells bearing or conveying water, whether the subject of private rights or otherwise, found or to be found in Nicosia Town or within a radius of five miles therefrom.

3. There shall be a Board (in this Law called "the Board") which shall be constituted as follows-
(a) the Commissioner of Nicosia, as chairman, who shall, in the case of equality of votes, have a casting vote in addition to his own vote;
(b) the Director of the Public Works Department;
(c) the Chairman of the High Council of Evcaf;
(d) the Mayor of Nicosia;
(e) one Councillor appointed by the Municipal Corporation of Nicosia.

15.-(1) The Board shall establish a fund to be called the Nicosia water supply fund into which all payments made by the Municipal Corporation of Nicosia and all charges levied and taken by the Board pursuant to Regulations made under this Law and all other moneys received by the Board shall be paid.
(2) Any moneys in the Nicosia water supply fund shall be applied by the Board in the following priority-
(a) for the repayment of any loan contracted by the Board under section 7;
(b)for the payment of compensation under section 6 or of any expenses incurred in connection with this Law;
(c) for the repayment of any moneys received from the Municipal Corporation of Nicosia under section 10.

16.-(1) It shall be the duty of the Board to make Regulations for all or any of the following matters-
(a)the administration of the Nicosia water supply fund and the manner of keeping, closing and auditing its accounts;
(b) the fixing of-
the percentage of any water the subject of private rights which may be taken, managed and controlled by the Board; and
the quantity of water to be supplied free of charge to any person or class of persons;
(c) the mode of managing and controlling the Nicosia water supply or any part thereof;
(d)the prevention of misuse, pollution or waste of the Nicosia water supplies or any part thereof;
(e)the scale of charges to be levied on and taken from any person for the use of water;
(f) the use of water for drinking and other domestic purposes.
(2) Regulations made under this section shall not be valid and effective until they are approved by the Governor and published in the Gazette.
